1ly.title: Bayesian updating
1ly.clickbait: Bayesian updating: the ideal way to change probabilistic beliefs based on evidence.
1ly.text: *Bayesian updating* or *Bayesian belief revision* is a way of changing probabilistic beliefs, in response to evidence, in a way that obeys [1lz probability theory].  When a piece of evidence is more likely given one state of the world than another, we should quantitatively shift our beliefs toward thinking more that we're in that world that was more likely to have produced the evidence.   Suppose there are two suspects in a murder, and that we previously thought that suspect #1 was twice as likely to have committed the murder as suspect #2.  If we then find a cryptic message at the crime scene, and we think suspect #1 was three times as likely to have left this message as suspect #2, our posterior belief should be that suspect #1 is six times as likely to have committed the murder as suspect #2.
